# UI Principles

- Follow Mobile First.
- Desktop should enhance—not replace—the mobile experience.

## Responsive

| Breakpoint | Width |
|------------|-------|
| Mobile | 390px |
| Tablet | 768px |
| Desktop | 1440px |

- Use CSS Grid and Flexbox.
- Never use fixed widths unless necessary.

## Design Tokens

All design values live in `tokens/` at the project root. Never hardcode colors, spacing, or typography in components.

```
tokens/
├── colors.json
├── typography.json
├── spacing.json
├── radius.json
├── shadows.json
├── motion.json
├── layout.json
├── z-index.json
├── breakpoints.json
├── semantic.json
└── index.json
```

- Use **semantic tokens** (`semantic.json`) in components — e.g. `button.primaryBg`, `card.border`.
- Reference raw tokens (`colors.json`, `spacing.json`) only in theme/config layers.
- Map tokens to CSS variables at build time (Tailwind theme or `globals.css`).
- Light and dark themes share the same token structure; swap values via `data-theme` or `.dark`.

## Layout

- 12-column grid.
- Max width: 1280px.
- Large whitespace.
- Consistent spacing.
- 8pt spacing system.

## Components

- Reusable.
- Accessible.
- Responsive.
- Consistent variants.
- No duplicate components.

## Buttons

- Primary
- Secondary
- Ghost
- Outline
- Icon

## Cards

- Consistent padding.
- Consistent radius.
- Consistent elevation.

## Icons

- Lucide React only.
- Outline icons.
- 2px stroke.

## Images

- Lazy load.
- Rounded corners.
- Proper aspect ratios.

## Animations

- Subtle.
- Purposeful.
- Never decorative.
- Use Framer Motion.
- Use GSAP only for scroll storytelling.
- Use CSS transitions where possible.

| Context | Duration |
|---------|----------|
| Hover | 200ms |
| Page | 300ms |

- Avoid excessive animation.

## Theme

- Light
- Dark
- Use CSS variables.
- No duplicated themes.
